# Cursor entrypoint

This repo uses a split CSS architecture. Do not assume a single `globals.css` stylesheet.

Before editing any UI:
- read [UI_CHANGE_PROTOCOL.md](/Users/oceancheung/Documents/Startup/MM.S/z_misc./Doom%20Scrolling%20Jobs/UI_CHANGE_PROTOCOL.md)
- read [AGENTS.md](/Users/oceancheung/Documents/Startup/MM.S/z_misc./Doom%20Scrolling%20Jobs/AGENTS.md)
- read [DESIGN.md](/Users/oceancheung/Documents/Startup/MM.S/z_misc./Doom%20Scrolling%20Jobs/DESIGN.md)
- follow the scoped rules in `.cursor/rules/`

Non-negotiables:
- preserve the current visual layout unless the request explicitly changes it
- prefer shared contract fixes over local overrides
- do not edit generated artifacts (`.next`, `.next 2`, caches, traces)
- verify every affected route after CSS or TSX changes
